<subSubSection id="C3438BE7FFA0FF909C91C5C88C51FEFA" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE6D86CFFA0FF909C91C5C88C51FEFA" blockId="115.[151,1436,151,258]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFFA0FF909C91C5C88853FF21" bold="true" box="[198,312,191,217]" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">Remarks</emphasis>
. The relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFFA0FF909E69C5B78B89FF21" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1907" box="[574,738,192,217]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calcarifera">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFFA0FF909E69C5B78B89FF21" box="[574,738,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">E. calcarifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unclear beyond inclusion within the monophyletic lineage of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C59A3EFFFA0FF909D48C59F88D7FEF9" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[287,444,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="115" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ephippiata">
<emphasis id="B92D047EFFA0FF909D48C59F88D7FEF9" box="[287,444,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="115" pageNumber="116">E. ephippiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group sharing completely fused cerci (see “Discussion” for details).
</paragraph>
